<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <p>The Pharmacy First Scotland service means your pharmacist can assess and treat a range of conditions on the NHS. You don't need to see a GP first — just walk in or call your local pharmacy.</p>

  <h2>Conditions treated under Pharmacy First Scotland</h2>
  <p>Pharmacists can prescribe treatment for these seven conditions:</p>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6 not-prose">
    {% set pharmacyFirstConditions = [
      "Urinary tract infection (UTI) in women aged 16–65",
      "Impetigo (skin infection)",
      "Shingles",
      "Sinusitis",
      "Sore throat",
      "Earache in children aged 1–17",
      "Infected insect bites"
    ] %}
    {% for condition in pharmacyFirstConditions %}
    <div class="flex items-start gap-2 bg-brand-light rounded p-3 text-sm">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 12.75l6 6 9-13.5"/>
      </svg>
      <span>{{ condition }}</span>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <h2>Other conditions your pharmacy can help with</h2>
  <p>Under the NHS Minor Ailment Service, pharmacists can also advise on and supply treatments for many other everyday conditions — for free if you hold a valid exemption certificate, or at a standard prescription charge:</p>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6 not-prose">
    {% set minorAilments = [
      "Athlete's foot",
      "Allergies and hay fever",
      "Backache and minor aches and pains",
      "Cold sores",
      "Conjunctivitis (minor eye conditions)",
      "Constipation",
      "Diarrhoea",
      "Eczema (mild)",
      "Head lice",
      "Indigestion and heartburn",
      "Mouth ulcers",
      "Oral thrush",
      "Period pains",
      "Threadworms",
      "Verrucas and warts"
    ] %}
