  <h2>Emergency contraception</h2>
  <p>Free emergency contraception is available from most pharmacies in Scotland without a prescription or GP appointment. This includes the morning-after pill (up to 72 hours after unprotected sex). Ask your pharmacist in confidence.</p>

  <h2>How to use Pharmacy First</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Visit or call your local pharmacy.</li>
    <li>Tell them you'd like to use the Pharmacy First service.</li>
    <li>The pharmacist will assess your condition — they may ask some questions in a private consultation room.</li>
    <li>They may be able to treat you there and then, or refer you to another service if needed.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>The service is free of charge on the NHS. You do not need a prescription or referral from us.</p>

  <h2>Find a local pharmacy</h2>
  <p>Use the <a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/scotlands-service-directory/pharmacy" rel="noopener noreferrer">NHS Inform pharmacy finder</a> to find a pharmacy near you.</p>

